  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite limited visibility in academic and public discourse, \"Brokers of Modernity,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2019, reflects scholarly interest, notably through its inferred commercial linkage evidenced by listings on platforms like Amazon and Goodreads.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Released in 2019 by Leuven University Press, \"Brokers of Modernity\" contributes to the understanding of modernity through a scholarly lens, though it currently has not gained significant traction in terms of citations or public engagement. However, the book\u2019s inferred commercial linkage indicates that it has been included in prominent retail and review sites, which may point to an audience drawn from both academic and non-academic circles.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">The work's lack of citations and mentions across various platforms can suggest a number of interpretations. On one hand, it represents a niche area of study that may not have yet resonated broadly within the academic community; on the other hand, the absence of public discussion threads on platforms such as Reddit or Wikipedia indicates that it has yet to spark significant societal dialogue or interest.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">Interestingly, the book is noted for its relevance to policy and sustainability, which is reflected in its connection to one Sustainable Development Goal. This indicates a recognition of the work's potential impact on contemporary issues, although scholarly uptake remains minimal, with only a handful of citations reported.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">In summary, while \"Brokers of Modernity\" does not currently display robust engagement metrics, its commercial linkage suggests that the work possesses a latent potential for broader academic and public discourse. Continuing to track its uptake may reveal shifts in interest and relevance as societal conversations evolve.</p>",
